Here is the translation:

"Makku Mado Bhilo Devo Hiro, Surji Khimo Bhakt Sudhira; 
Narayana Adi Bahu Bhai, Sundar Ratan Ne Ganga Bai."

This is the original couplet:

Ah ahadi bai bhai ghanan, sarve sevak che swami tanan;
Rhe burenapure e jan, kare Swamishreejini nu bhajan.

Translated to English:

These are the first brothers many, all servants are of Lord; 
He resides in Bhurana-pura, and performs devotion to Lord Swamishreejini.

The two lines are:

DviJ mayārām nē ēkāra, bhakt ānjanō dudō Udāra;
Eh vase gāma mīnmāņī, bhaje Svāmī jānī Sukhadāi.
